sinopsis: A new FBI profiler, Elizabeth Keen, has her entire life uprooted when a mysterious criminal, Raymond Reddington, who has eluded capture for decades, turns himself in and insists on speaking only to her.

episodios.sinopsis: A brilliant fugitive surrenders to the FBI and offers to help them hunt down the world's most dangerous criminals, but only if he can work with a rookie profiler.
Red directs the FBI to a killer who disguises his murders as everyday accidents; Liz tries to hide Tom's secret.
Liz and the FBI hunt for a Chinese spy that Red says has been sent to kill a CIA agent.
The team hunts a chemical weapons specialist known as "The Stewmaker," who uses chemicals to dissolve his victims.
Red tells Liz and Ressler that The Courier, a messenger who cannot be caught, is delivering a package worth millions to a spy.
When Red points the FBI to a corporate terrorist, Liz discovers a connection to Tom.
A former government scientist unleashes a rare, deadly disease, prompting Liz and the task force to race against time to find him and a cure.
The team tracks an anti-capitalist group targeting the U.S. financial system; Liz gets a major break in her investigation of Tom.
An old nemesis of Red's, Anslo Garrick, infiltrates the FBI black site and attempts to capture him.
As Liz and Red fight for their lives against Anslo Garrick's siege on the FBI black site, Liz uncovers new information about Red's past.
Red helps Liz and the FBI track down a vigilante killer who targets abusive individuals.
The team hunts a man who uses science to transform people's DNA; Liz continues to investigate Tom.
Liz uncovers an illegal adoption organization that may have ties to Red; Red demands a deal from Cooper.
Liz helps Red track a beautiful and dangerous woman from his past who is involved in stealing a nuclear weapon.
A former prosecutor goes on a killing spree, forcing Red to confront his past with the man.
Red informs the team that a ruthless Yakuza crime boss, Mako Tanida, has escaped from prison and is seeking revenge.
The team hunts for a cyber terrorist who has stolen a classified list of U.S. intelligence assets.
Red and Liz investigate a Blacklister who manipulates ordinary people into becoming killers.
The team targets a Serbian family of kidnappers known as the Pavlovich Brothers, who are abducting a scientist.
Red helps the FBI find a political manipulator who is behind a series of assassinations.
The team faces their most formidable foe yet, a mysterious criminal mastermind known only as Berlin.
In the explosive season finale, Liz discovers a shocking truth about her past as Red confronts Berlin.
Reddington faces a new threat from a man named Lord Baltimore. Liz tries to move on from her relationship with Tom.
The task force investigates a high-end bank for criminals. Red continues his hunt for Berlin.
The team pursues a doctor who is part of an illegal organ harvesting ring.
Reddington alerts the FBI to a scientist who is experimenting on patients, turning them into killers.

Reddington finally confronts Berlin, leading to a tense showdown and revelations about Berlin's past.

With Liz on the run, Reddington and the task force race to clear her name and expose Tom Connolly and the Cabal.
On the run, Liz and Red seek help from a blacklister known as the Troll Farmer to disappear. The task force, led by Ressler, hunts them down.
Red enlists the help of a lawyer, Marvin Gerard, to help clear Liz's name. Ressler closes in on Liz.
Liz and Red investigate a scientist who is bio-engineering crops, while the Cabal puts a bounty on Liz's head.
Red and Liz seek out a blacklister known as The Djinn, who fulfills revenge fantasies.
The task force hunts a blacklister who uses a sophisticated computer program to track and kill former members of the Cabal.
Red and Liz investigate a billionaire who is secretly abducting brilliant scientists for a mysterious project.

Reddington executes a daring plan to exonerate Liz and expose the Director and the Cabal.
A man claiming to be Raymond Reddington turns himself in to the FBI, creating chaos for Red and the task force.
The task force investigates a medieval cult that is murdering people they deem sinners.
Red and Liz target a blacklister known as the 'negotiator' who brokers deals between rival criminal organizations.
The team hunts a woman who abducts children she believes are unwanted.

Red enlists Tom and the task force to help track a notorious bounty hunter who may lead them to Agnes.

Red and Liz pursue a blacklister who transmits a deadly disease through touch.

Liz finally confronts Ian Garvey, leading to a dramatic showdown and the revelation of the contents of the mysterious duffel bag.
Reddington puts the task force on the case of a blacklister who is a master of disguise.
Liz and the task force hunt a blacklister who is targeting witnesses in a major criminal trial.

The task force hunts a blacklister who is using genetically modified insects to commit murder.
Liz and Jennifer continue their search for the truth about Red's identity, while Red navigates the dangers of prison.
Reddington, still in prison, helps the task force investigate a blacklister who is leaking classified government secrets.

sinopsis: An antisocial maverick doctor who specializes in diagnostic medicine does whatever it takes to solve puzzling cases that come his way using his crack team of doctors and his wits.

episodios.sinopsis: Dr. House and his team try to diagnose a kindergarten teacher who begins speaking gibberish and collapses in class.
A 16-year-old lacrosse player is plagued by night terrors and double vision following a concussion.
A college student collapses after a frat party, suffering from extreme nausea and disorientation.
Newborns in the hospital's maternity ward fall critically ill from a mysterious, spreading infection.
A nun arrives at the clinic with symptoms resembling stigmata, which House believes is an allergic reaction.
A mother with schizophrenia develops a DVT, though her son claims she hasn't left the couch.
A woman has African sleeping sickness, but neither she nor her husband has ever been to Africa.
A high school student collapses with severe symptoms; House suspects poisoning but the source is unknown.
A legendary jazz musician with ALS collapses but has signed a DNR; House suspects a misdiagnosis.
House treats a homeless woman with a serious illness and a hidden past who refuses treatment.
House treats a teen girl whose illness might be linked to her boyfriend's death, all while trying to detox from Vicodin.
A famous baseball pitcher breaks his arm, but House suspects an underlying condition causing bone fragility.
A young boy believes he's cursed after multiple misfortunes and illnesses plague his family.
A successful CEO experiences sudden paralysis in her legs, leading to a clash with House over her treatment.
A man in witness protection collapses, and his mobster brother attempts to control his medical care.
A morbidly obese 10-year-old girl suffers a heart attack; House clashes with her mother over the cause.
A black presidential candidate falls ill during a fundraiser, putting House's team under political pressure.
Vogler forces House to fire a team member; a pregnant woman with cancer presents an ethical dilemma.
A 12-year-old diving champion suffers a mysterious illness, forcing House to confront issues related to children.
House treats a patient who had a stroke after an S&M session, complicated by the patient's secrecy.
House lectures students using three cases of leg pain, revealing his own medical history and infarction.
House's ex-girlfriend, Stacy Warner, asks him to diagnose her husband, Mark, who is mysteriously ill.
House deals with Stacy's presence while treating a death row inmate who collapsed after hallucinating.
House and his team must diagnose a nine-year-old cancer patient who begins hallucinating.
Cuddy's handyman falls from her roof and develops a mysterious infection. House suspects Cuddy is hiding something.
A famous doctor known for his work in Africa collapses. House suspects TB, but the case is more complex.
A recent college graduate suffers a seizure at his graduation party. His father's presence complicates the diagnosis.
A professional cyclist admits to blood doping and then collapses. House must find the real cause of his illness.
A gay man with AIDS develops pneumonia, but his symptoms don't match typical complications.
Chase is sued after a patient dies, and House must testify. The case revisits a past mistake by Chase.
A woman fakes seizures to get Vicodin. House is intrigued by her ability to mimic symptoms perfectly.
A journalist collapses and develops aphasia. House tries to communicate with him to find the diagnosis.
A woman suffers from uncontrollable muscle spasms. House suspects her perfect life is hiding a secret.
House treats a teenager with severe burns who develops an unrelated, mysterious illness. He also tries to impress Stacy.
A teenage supermodel collapses on the runway. House suspects drug use, but the truth is more complex.
An elderly woman contracts a sexually transmitted disease, leading House to investigate her romantic life.
A man suffers respiratory failure during role-playing with his wife. House believes the wife is poisoning him.
A teenage girl with a recently transplanted heart collapses after an allergic reaction.
House treats a 6-year-old boy with symptoms mirroring a previous case House couldn't solve.
A young woman suffers from chronic insomnia, leading to dangerous health complications.
A 15-year-old faith healer is admitted with symptoms that challenge House's atheism.
Foreman contracts a mysterious illness from a police officer patient, leading to rapidly progressing symptoms.
With Foreman's condition worsening and blindness setting in, House desperately tries to find a diagnosis and cure.
A new mother suffers a seizure while bathing her baby, leading House to suspect postpartum psychosis.
A young woman, a victim of Hurricane Katrina, hallucinates. House is intrigued by her claims of knowing her father.
House is shot by a former patient's husband and experiences vivid hallucinations while being treated.
Recovering from gunshot wounds, House takes on two cases simultaneously: a paralyzed man and a woman with unexplained seizures.
A seven-year-old boy who claims to have been abducted by aliens is admitted with rectal bleeding.
A renowned medical researcher collapses in his lab. He demands to be euthanized if his condition is terminal.
An autistic boy screams incessantly. House moves into Wilson's apartment due to a patient's complaint.
A young woman is admitted with heart problems after her husband suddenly collapses and dies.
A morbidly obese man is found in a coma and refuses all tests unless House can prove his weight isn't the cause.
House tries to awaken a man in a persistent vegetative state to get his family medical history for his ill son.
An 18-year-old caregiver for his two younger siblings suffers a heart attack and a series of other ailments.
A young girl is admitted with pancreatitis after her parents ignore House's advice for a different diagnosis.
Wilson negotiates a deal for House to get his Vicodin back as House treats a girl with a collapsed lung.
A firefighter hero is admitted with disorientation and extreme body temperature fluctuations. House faces an arraignment.
House is forced to work in the clinic, where he encounters a rape victim who challenges his detachment.
A Romani teenager is admitted with respiratory distress; his family's distrust of medicine complicates treatment.
A teenage girl who cannot feel pain is admitted after a car accident, posing unique diagnostic challenges.
A musical savant with severe brain damage suffers a seizure. House suspects he's faking his condition.
A Marine returning from Iraq suffers from symptoms resembling Gulf War Syndrome, but House suspects otherwise.
A pregnant photographer collapses during an assignment. House recommends a risky surgery that could save her or the baby.
On a flight back from a conference, House and Cuddy must diagnose an outbreak of a mysterious illness among passengers.
A six-year-old girl exhibits symptoms of adult illnesses, leading the team to suspect precocious puberty.
A young woman who dedicates her life to charity work becomes ill, forcing Foreman to make a difficult decision.
A young boy needs a bone marrow transplant from his older brother, but the older brother also falls ill.
A college student attempts suicide and is found to have an underlying illness. Foreman announces his resignation.
A teenage chess prodigy with severe behavioral problems collapses during a tournament.
A Cuban couple makes a dangerous journey to the U.S. for House to diagnose the wife's heart condition. The team disbands.
With his team gone, House tries to diagnose a young woman who survived an office building collapse.
House begins a 'Survivor'-style competition to choose his new team while treating a female fighter pilot.
The fellowship candidates compete to diagnose a man with spinal muscular atrophy who suddenly becomes paralyzed.
A funeral home cosmetician believes she's being visited by the spirits of the dead and has seizures.
A man with a rare condition causing him to mirror others' personalities is admitted. Foreman returns to the team.
House is recruited by the CIA to diagnose an ill agent, while the candidates treat a race car driver.
A teenager with a severe facial deformity undergoing reconstructive surgery develops complications.

episodios.titulo: T4:E8 - You Don't Want to Know
episodios.sinopsis: A magician whose heart stops during an underwater escape trick is admitted. House narrows down his team.
A rebellious punk rock musician collapses after a show. House uses an unorthodox method to choose his final two fellows.
A woman with sudden paralysis in her hands won't tell the truth, hindering her diagnosis. House finalizes his new team.
A psychiatrist stationed at the South Pole falls ill, and House must diagnose and treat her via webcam.
A recently converted Hasidic Jewish woman collapses at her wedding. Her new lifestyle choices complicate diagnosis.

episodios.titulo: T4:E13 - No More Mr. Nice Guy
episodios.sinopsis: House suspects an ER patient, who is unusually nice, has a serious illness linked to his pleasant demeanor.
House believes his favorite soap opera actor is seriously ill, despite the actor's claims of being healthy.
House survives a bus crash with amnesia and must piece together his memories to identify a dying fellow passenger.
Continuing from the bus crash, Wilson's girlfriend Amber is revealed as the mystery patient, and her life hangs in the balance.
Wilson resigns from the hospital following Amber's death, while House deals with his guilt and tries to save a woman's job.
House investigates a series of organ transplant recipients who are dying from an unknown ailment.
A painter whose distorted vision influences his art suffers a seizure. House uses a P.I. to spy on his team and Wilson.
House is forced on a road trip with Wilson to his father's funeral, while the team diagnoses a woman with a mysterious past.
Thirteen's one-night stand falls ill, forcing her to confront her own Huntington's diagnosis and reckless behavior.
A middle-aged woman suffering from sleepwalking and other symptoms also wants to give up her newborn baby.
House treats an agoraphobic man who refuses to leave his home, forcing the team to work remotely.
A 16-year-old factory manager, recently emancipated, collapses. Foreman takes on his own pediatric case.
A man takes House, Thirteen, and several patients hostage, demanding a diagnosis for his own mysterious condition.
A fitness guru collapses. Thirteen starts experimental Huntington's treatment with Foreman's help.
A bullied teenager collapses during a Christmas program. House and the team deal with holiday-related issues.
A man suffering from chronic, debilitating pain contemplates suicide, forcing House to confront his own pain.
A special education teacher who is overly nice collapses. Cuddy tries to balance work and motherhood.
A former cancer researcher who quit her job to pursue happiness collapses. Thirteen's condition worsens.
A priest who runs a homeless shelter questions his faith after falling ill. House deals with his insomnia.
A couple with an intersex child has differing opinions on gender assignment surgery when the child falls ill.
A book editor with a split personality collapses. House's lack of sleep causes him to be unusually honest.
A nursing home worker believes a cat can predict death, and then she herself falls ill.
House treats a patient with locked-in syndrome, communicating only through eye movements, from the patient's POV.
An elderly woman caring for her dying husband collapses. The team is shocked by Kutner's sudden death.
An environmental activist collapses during a protest. Cameron postpones her vacation with Chase to stay on the case.
A deaf wrestler hears explosions in his head. House hallucinates Amber and struggles with his Vicodin addiction.
A ballerina's lungs collapse. House tries to detox from Vicodin to stop his hallucinations of Amber.
A man whose left and right brain hemispheres act independently is admitted. House's detox seems successful, leading to a night with Cuddy, but his sanity unravels.
House commits himself to a psychiatric hospital to get off Vicodin, where he clashes with the staff and fellow patients.
House returns to Princeton-Plainsboro but struggles without his medical license. Foreman leads the team on a case involving a video game creator.
The team treats a ruthless African dictator. House, still unlicensed, tries to manipulate Foreman's handling of the case.
A wealthy businessman believes his sudden illness is karmic retribution for his son's accidental death.
A police officer with a family history of sudden cardiac death collapses. Chase worries about his upcoming wedding to Cameron.
A teenage girl with severely swollen limbs is admitted. House, Wilson, and Cuddy attend a medical conference where secrets are revealed.
House gets his medical license back and tries to reassemble his old team to treat an adult film star.
A brilliant physicist gives up his career to work as a courier and live a simpler life, then falls ill.
The episode focuses on Wilson as he treats an old friend and former patient who is dying of cancer.
An undercover cop posing as a drug dealer collapses. House suspects one of his team members is poisoning him.
A businesswoman with an unusually high level of empathy for others falls ill. Thirteen considers a risky career move.
A college football player with NFL ambitions collapses. Foreman's brother is released from prison.
The episode follows Cuddy through a challenging day balancing hospital administration, patient care, and personal life.
An avid blogger who shares every detail of her life online is admitted with a mysterious illness.
A high school student hallucinates and collapses. House and Wilson attend a speed dating event.
The hospital is locked down due to a missing infant, trapping House with a patient and others in various locations.
A knight in a Renaissance fair collapses. Wilson starts dating his first ex-wife.
A woman in an open marriage suddenly falls ill. Taub struggles with his own marital issues.
A man gives up his high-powered career to pursue his dream of being a writer, then falls ill.
House recounts his week to his therapist, including a patient who has amnesia and only a few possessions.
House joins a rescue effort at a disaster site where a crane collapsed, and tries to save a trapped woman.
