House and Cuddy explore their new relationship while the team tries to find a neurosurgeon for the hospital when one falls ill.
A teenage skateboarder with a genetic condition collapses. House and Cuddy's relationship impacts their work.
A popular children's author attempts suicide and is admitted. House tries to hide his relationship with Cuddy from the team.
A woman suffers a severe allergic reaction. House hires a new female doctor, Martha Masters.
A newborn baby suffers from breathing problems and liver failure. Cuddy's mother meddles in her relationship with House.
A political campaign manager for a New Jersey senator falls ill with liver failure. Cuddy forces House to hire a female doctor.

episodios.titulo: T7:E7 - A Pox on Our House
episodios.sinopsis: A 200-year-old medicine jar found on a shipwreck may be linked to a modern-day illness involving a father and daughter.
A man is admitted after re-enacting the crucifixion. He refuses treatment for religious reasons.
A man known for his heroic actions collapses while saving a woman from a subway track.
A drill sergeant collapses. Taub's ex-wife makes a surprising request. House tests Masters' ethics.
Cuddy's mother is admitted with mysterious symptoms, forcing House to navigate family dynamics and hospital politics.
A waitress with a perfect memory suffers temporary paralysis. Wilson tries to furnish his new condo.
Two students sent to the principal's office become ill. House tells their story to illustrate a point about Cuddy.
A man who lost his job and home during the recession becomes ill after trying to burn down his repossessed house.
Cuddy faces a health scare, leading to surreal dream sequences involving House and the team. Thirteen returns.
A professional bull rider is admitted after being attacked by a bull. House deals with the aftermath of Cuddy's illness.
A homeless man who was once a successful executive is admitted after displaying bizarre symptoms.
House helps Thirteen with a personal matter after her release from prison, revealing why she was incarcerated.
Masters faces her final days as a medical student and must decide whether to join House's team permanently.
A lottery winner searching for his long-lost love collapses. Cuddy's mother sues the hospital.
A talented scientist working on a new explosive device falls ill. House becomes obsessed with a boxing match.
Thirteen helps a friend with a drug problem. House takes a risky experimental drug to regenerate his leg muscle.
A performance artist with self-inflicted symptoms challenges the team. House makes a life-altering decision after Cuddy breaks up with him.
House is in prison after driving his car into Cuddy's house. He must find a way to get Vicodin and solve a fellow inmate's medical mystery.
Released from prison, House returns to a very different Princeton-Plainsboro and treats an organ recipient whose new lung is failing.
A wealthy philanthropist collapses after making a large donation. House is intrigued by his extreme altruism.
A CEO falls ill days before signing a controversial business deal. Park prepares for her hearing with the hospital disciplinary committee.
A respected community man collapses and confesses to past sins, shocking his family and complicating his diagnosis.
A young man trying to follow in his deceased father's footsteps as an entertainer collapses. House's parents are in town.
The team treats a 14-year-old girl with anaphylaxis. House becomes obsessed with a case Foreman wants him to drop.
An assistant U.S. Attorney suffers a heart attack, but House suspects he's being poisoned due to paranoia.
An Alzheimer's patient suffering from violent outbursts is admitted. Wilson tries to prove House has a new best friend.
A homeless teenage girl is admitted with ear pain and bleeding. Foreman's romantic relationship is challenged.
House faces a disciplinary hearing after a violent incident with a patient puts his medical license at risk.
Chase takes on the case of a cloistered nun about to take her final vows, and forms a unique connection with her.
A marriage counselor collapses during a seminar. House and his Ukrainian 'wife' Dominika try to convince immigration she's legitimate.
A blind man falls ill shortly after asking his girlfriend to marry him. House's mother delivers surprising news.
A soldier charged with treason after leaking classified information collapses. Adams suspects House is seriously ill.
An amateur hockey player collapses after coughing up blood on the ice. Wilson tries to hide a secret from House.
A man who weeps blood is admitted. House and Dominika's relationship takes an unexpected turn.
A young boy has recurring nightmares about being choked, then develops respiratory distress. Wilson reveals his cancer diagnosis to House.
Wilson undergoes aggressive chemotherapy. The team treats a 6-year-old girl with a rare genetic condition whose mother is a doctor.
Dr. Peter Treiber, the pathologist who replaced Chase, is found dead in the lab. House suspects foul play.
A college student with hearing voices and visions is admitted. Wilson makes a decision about his remaining time.
Facing returning to prison and Wilson's impending death, House treats a drug-addicted patient and contemplates his own life and future.

sinopsis: A famous "psychic" outs himself as a fake, and starts working as a consultant for the California Bureau of Investigation so he can find "Red John", the madman who killed his wife and daughter.

episodios.sinopsis: Patrick Jane, a former fake psychic, uses his keen powers of observation to help the CBI solve the murder of a professional golfer's wife and a doctor.

episodios.titulo: T1:E2 - Red Hair and Silver Tape
episodios.sinopsis: A young woman is found murdered in a vineyard. Patrick Jane uses his unique methods to profile the killer and help the CBI team solve the case.
A young surfer girl is found dead on the beach, and the CBI is called in to investigate what appears to be a drowning, but Patrick suspects foul play.
A wealthy investment banker is found murdered in his locked panic room. Jane sets a mentalist trap to expose the killer among the victim's family and associates.
A girl is found murdered, and her friend is missing. The CBI team investigates if the missing girl is a victim or a suspect, while Jane observes the family.
The severed hand of a casino owner is found in the desert. Jane uses his skills to navigate the world of high-stakes gambling to find the killer.
A wealthy socialite, who was also a supposed psychic, is murdered. Jane clashes with another psychic involved in the case, challenging her abilities.
A state trooper is murdered, and the local sheriff's department seems uncooperative. Jane suspects a cover-up within the small town's law enforcement.
An arson attack kills a National Guard soldier at his home. The CBI investigates whether it was a random act or targeted murder.
A university professor known for his controversial research is poisoned. Jane delves into academic politics and rivalries to find the killer.
A man claims he has information about Red John to lure Jane into helping him prove his innocence in a murder case. Jane is forced to confront his past.
A high school football star is murdered, and the local community is in shock. Jane uncovers secrets and lies among the students and faculty.
The CEO of a software company is murdered by a valuable painting being dropped on his head. Jane stages an art auction to flush out the killer.
A womanizer is found murdered in his home. Jane sets up a romantic trap to catch the killer among the victim's many lovers.
A debutante is poisoned at her own coming-out party. The CBI team navigates the world of high society to find the murderer.
Jane is temporarily blinded by an explosion while investigating a murder at a financial firm. He must rely on his other senses to solve the case.
A group of corporate executives on a wilderness retreat are targeted by a killer. Jane uses the isolated setting to his advantage.
A hypnotist helps a woman recover her memory of a murder, but Jane is skeptical of his methods and suspects he may be involved.
A movie producer is found dead in his home. The investigation leads Jane and the team into the glamorous but deceitful world of Hollywood.
A former mobster in witness protection is murdered. Jane must uncover secrets from his past life to find the killer.
The CEO of a company that develops navigation software for yachts is murdered aboard his boat. Jane finds clues among the corporate elite.
A troubled young man at a wilderness program for at-risk youth is found dead. Jane investigates the program's unconventional methods and its students.
Red John strikes again, taunting Jane and the CBI. The investigation leads to a blind woman who may have encountered Red John.
While the CBI investigates a murder where the key witness is suffering from amnesia, Jane is reassigned to a new team after his actions in the Red John case.
A state senator's intern is found murdered. The investigation uncovers a political scandal and illicit affairs.
Lisbon is accused of murdering a child molester she put away years ago, and Jane must prove her innocence.
A powerful lawyer connected to a notorious biker gang is murdered. Jane goes undercover within the gang to find the killer.
A modern-day gold prospector is found murdered near his claim. The CBI team uncovers a web of greed and betrayal in a small mining town.
A former financial advisor, now living off the grid, is murdered. Jane investigates his past connections to wealthy clients.

episodios.titulo: T2:E7 - Black Gold and Red Blood
episodios.sinopsis: The murder of an oil tycoon brings the CBI into the high-stakes world of energy speculation and family feuds.
The CBI investigates a triple homicide that appears to be the work of Red John, but Jane suspects a copycat or a trap.
A wealthy jewelry store owner is murdered during a heist. Jane uses his knowledge of con artistry to solve the crime.
A former professional baseball player, now a scout, is found murdered. Jane explores the competitive world of sports and player recruitment.
A wealthy couple is murdered at a high school reunion. Jane attends the reunion undercover to find the killer among the nostalgic attendees.
A mayor's aide is found murdered during a controversial development project. The CBI team navigates local politics and environmental activism.
A beautiful saleswoman at a luxury car dealership is murdered. Jane investigates the high-pressure sales environment and the victim's complicated life.
A former gang member trying to turn his life around is murdered. Rigsby is forced to confront his own past connections to the gang world.
A renowned chef is poisoned at his own restaurant. Jane uses his culinary knowledge to uncover secrets in the competitive gourmet world.
A bio-weapon is released at a research facility, and the CBI team is quarantined inside with a potential killer and the deadly virus.
An antique box with mysterious contents becomes the key to solving the murder of its owner, a reclusive academic.
The murder of a brilliant mathematician leads Jane and the team into the world of corporate espionage and complex algorithms.
A district attorney is murdered on the eve of a major trial. The CBI investigates if the killing is connected to the case or a personal vendetta.
The head of a media conglomerate is murdered. Jane uses the company's own news network to manipulate suspects and uncover the truth.
A documentarian making a film about a cult is murdered. Jane infiltrates the cult to find the killer among its charismatic leader and devoted followers.
The director of a controversial organization that debunks psychics is murdered, and Jane becomes a prime suspect.

episodios.titulo: T2:E23 - Red Sky in the Morning
episodios.sinopsis: Red John resurfaces, playing a deadly game with Jane by involving a new psychic, Kristina Frye, who claims to be in contact with him.
Following his encounter with Red John, Jane reconsiders his future with the CBI while dealing with the aftermath and Lisbon's concern for him.
Jane's estranged brother-in-law, a con artist, becomes entangled in a murder case, forcing Jane to confront his family's past.

episodios.titulo: T3:E3 - The Blood on His Hands
episodios.sinopsis: The leader of a Visualize cult is murdered, and the CBI investigates the secretive organization. Rosalind Harker, Red John's former blind lover, reappears.
A former convict trying to start a new life is murdered. Jane uses his skills to determine if the past caught up with him or if something new led to his death.
A jockey is murdered, and Jane delves into the competitive and often corrupt world of horse racing to find the killer.
The patriarch of a wealthy and powerful family is murdered. The CBI uncovers long-buried secrets and rivalries among the heirs.
A wealthy businessman is killed by a car bomb. The investigation points to a notorious hitman, but Jane suspects a more personal motive.
Jane is kidnapped by a woman who believes he is responsible for her brother's death, a case from Jane's psychic days.
A triple homicide in a small farming town appears to be the work of a werewolf. Jane uses the local legend to his advantage.
A Santa Claus impersonator is murdered during the holiday season. Jane investigates the world of professional Santas.
A mixed martial arts fighter is murdered before a major bout. Jane delves into the brutal and competitive world of MMA.
A rival consultant with a more scientific approach is brought in on a double murder case, creating a clash of methods with Jane.
A software designer is murdered by a drone strike. The CBI team investigates a high-tech world of cyber warfare and defense contractors.
A key witness in a murder trial is killed, and Van Pelt goes undercover at a police academy to find the mole.
The owner of a failing gold mine is found dead. Jane investigates whether it was an accident or murder tied to a rumored new gold strike.
A museum director is murdered, and a valuable artifact is stolen. The investigation leads to a connection with Red John and his network.
A doctor is murdered at a hospital. Jane uses unconventional methods to observe the staff and patients, suspecting the killer is still among them.
A man wrongly convicted of murder is released, only to be killed shortly after. Jane investigates if the original killer struck again or if a new motive arose.

episodios.titulo: T3:E19 - Every Rose Has Its Thorn
episodios.sinopsis: A matchmaker is murdered, and Jane investigates her clients, suspecting one of them was led to a deadly encounter.
A tech company whistleblower is murdered. The CBI team sifts through classified information and corporate secrets.
A prison guard is murdered within a correctional facility. Jane goes undercover as an inmate to find the killer.
A talented violinist is murdered, and the investigation leads Jane into the competitive and passionate world of classical music.
Jane and the CBI are targeted by a bomber. The investigation reveals a mole within the CBI working for Red John.
As the mole's identity is revealed, Jane finally comes face-to-face with a man he believes to be Red John, leading to a shocking confrontation.
Jane is in jail following his public execution of the man he believed to be Red John, and must prove his actions were justified or face murder charges.
A personal trainer is murdered. While Jane deals with being reinstated at the CBI, the team investigates the victim's clients and secrets.
A nine-year-old boy is kidnapped from his home, and his distraught mother pleads for Jane's help in finding him.
A photojournalist specializing in conflict zones is murdered. The investigation leads to a conspiracy involving powerful figures.
A woman is found murdered on an island off the coast of California. Jane and the CBI team investigate the small, isolated community.

episodios.titulo: T4:E6 - Where in the World Is Carmine O'Brien?
episodios.sinopsis: A police chief is murdered in a resort town. Jane observes the local law enforcement and tourists to find the killer.
A serial killer taunts the CBI by leaving clues related to Jane. The team races against time to stop the next murder.
An undercover narcotics officer is murdered. Jane investigates the dangerous world of drug trafficking and corrupt cops.
A former star quarterback is murdered on the eve of a charity game. Jane delves into the world of professional football and old rivalries.
After nearly drowning, Jane suffers from temporary amnesia, reverting to his former life as a con man psychic, much to the team's concern.
A casino employee is murdered. Jane uses his gambling skills and knowledge of human behavior to navigate the high-stakes world of a casino.
The son of a notorious mob boss is murdered. Jane investigates the complex dynamics of organized crime families.

episodios.titulo: T4:E13 - Red is the New Black
episodios.sinopsis: A fashion designer is murdered before a major show. Jane enters the competitive and cutthroat world of high fashion.
A woman is found murdered in a park, and the prime suspect is a man she met through online dating. Jane orchestrates a sting operation.
A divorce lawyer known for his aggressive tactics is murdered. Jane investigates his disgruntled former clients and bitter legal battles.

episodios.titulo: T4:E16 - His Thoughts Were Red Thoughts
episodios.sinopsis: The CBI investigates the murder of a man found dead at a Visualize cult compound, leading to renewed focus on Bret Stiles.
Jane and the CBI team investigate the murder of a popular saleswoman at a car dealership. Summer, Jane's CI, gets involved.
A cancer patient dies under suspicious circumstances at a cutting-edge research hospital. Jane investigates the doctors and their experimental treatments.
A casino employee is found dead in the Nevada desert after a wild party. The CBI team travels to investigate, and Rigsby has a run-in with his father.
An English teacher is murdered at a prestigious private high school. Jane uncovers secrets among the students and faculty.
A man dressed as a drag queen is murdered. Jane investigates the vibrant but often hidden world of drag performers.

episodios.titulo: T4:E22 - So Long, and Thanks for All the Red Snapper
episodios.sinopsis: A surfer is found murdered, and Jane suspects a connection to a local surf gang. Cho reconnects with Summer.
Jane receives a taunting message from Red John, leading him to re-examine a closed case that might hold clues to the killer's identity.
Jane orchestrates an elaborate plan to trap Red John, but it goes awry, leading to a shocking confrontation and consequences for the CBI team.
The CBI team investigates the murders of two motel employees, while Jane deals with the fallout from his Red John gambit and his relationship with Lorelei Martins.
While investigating the murder of a diamond cutter, Jane ingests a hallucinogenic tea and has visions of his deceased daughter.
A bank teller is murdered during a robbery. Jane observes the hostages and bank employees to find the killer among them.
Rigsby's father is found injured at a crime scene involving a turf war between rival gangs. Rigsby must confront his family issues.
A flashback episode reveals Jane's first day at the CBI and his initial interactions with Lisbon and the team, as they investigate a Red John-related murder.
The CBI investigates the kidnapping of a wealthy couple. Jane focuses on the seemingly cooperative son.

episodios.titulo: T5:E7 - If It Bleeds, It Leads
episodios.sinopsis: A TV news reporter investigating a human trafficking ring is murdered. Jane uses the media to manipulate suspects.

episodios.titulo: T5:E8 - Red Sails in the Sunset
episodios.sinopsis: Lorelei Martins escapes from prison, and Jane helps her evade the authorities, believing she can lead him to Red John.
A real estate agent with gang connections is murdered. The CBI investigates his ties to a local gang and a community redevelopment project.
A young botanist working at a high-tech marijuana research facility is murdered. Jane investigates the competitive world of cannabis cultivation.

episodios.titulo: T5:E11 - Days of Wine and Roses
episodios.sinopsis: A model is murdered during a photo shoot at a Napa Valley winery. Jane explores the glamorous but often troubled lives of those in the fashion industry.
The geologist of an old gold mining town is found dead. Jane and the CBI team delve into the town's secrets and legends.
The CBI investigates a 25-year-old cold case involving a massacre at a Visualize cult ranch that may have Red John connections.

episodios.titulo: T5:E14 - Red in Tooth and Claw
episodios.sinopsis: A student is murdered at a natural history museum. Jane sets a trap using the museum's exhibits to catch the killer.
An elderly heiress is found dead in her mansion, and her much younger husband is the prime suspect. Jane looks for clues within the opulent estate.
Lorelei Martins returns, seeking revenge on Red John for her sister's murder. Jane must decide how far he'll go to help her and get his own answers.
A soldier at an army base is murdered. Jane clashes with military protocol as he investigates the close-knit and disciplined community.
A popular stage actress is murdered during a performance. Jane investigates the world of theater, full of drama both on and off stage.
The owner of a Wild West tourist town is murdered. Jane uses the town's attractions to stage a showdown and expose the killer.
A woman who claimed to have been abducted by aliens is found murdered. Jane investigates the UFO enthusiast community.
A Homeland Security agent is murdered, and the investigation points to a dangerous computer hacker. Van Pelt reconnects with a former love interest.
Red John strikes again, and the victim has a connection to Jane's past. Jane reveals his list of seven Red John suspects to Lisbon.
Jane and Lisbon secretly continue their investigation into the seven Red John suspects, while the CBI team officially works on a new murder case.
The CBI investigates the murder of a software engineer. Jane continues to probe his Red John suspects, focusing on Bret Stiles.
A wedding turns deadly when a guest is murdered. Jane uses the chaotic celebration to observe the suspects, including one of his Red John list.
Someone is targeting individuals connected to Visualize. Jane must protect a Red John suspect on his list while trying to determine their guilt.
A prominent member of Visualize is found murdered, and Jane is convinced Red John is involved, trying to eliminate one of the suspects on his list.
Jane gathers the remaining Red John suspects in one place, hoping to finally unmask his nemesis. The confrontation takes an explosive turn.
In the aftermath of the explosion, the CBI headquarters are in chaos. The identity of Red John's accomplices within law enforcement begins to unravel.
With Red John's identity finally revealed, Patrick Jane engages in a final, deadly confrontation with the man who destroyed his life.
Two years after Red John's death, Jane is living a peaceful life in Mexico. The FBI, led by Agent Abbott, tracks him down with an offer he can't refuse.
Jane, now working with the FBI, helps investigate the murder of a computer programmer in a tech commune.
The FBI investigates a murder in a town known for its illegal drug trade. Jane uses his unique skills to navigate the dangerous environment.
A cartographer is murdered, and the investigation leads to a hidden treasure and a group of competitive treasure hunters.
The murder of a U.S. attorney in Mexico brings Jane and Lisbon across the border, where they encounter a dangerous drug cartel.
A man is found murdered on an oil rig. Jane and the FBI team investigate the isolated and dangerous world of offshore drilling.

episodios.titulo: T6:E15 - White as the Driven Snow
episodios.sinopsis: Grace Van Pelt is abducted by a killer targeting former CBI members. The team races against time to find her before it's too late.
Jane and Fischer go undercover at a high-end resort to investigate the murder of a woman who was part of an art theft ring.
A man on death row claims innocence just days before his execution. Jane re-examines the old case to find the truth.
A woman is found murdered in a remote forest, and the investigation leads to a group of illegal loggers and environmental activists.
The FBI investigates a human trafficking ring after several young women go missing. Jane uses his observation skills to track the victims.
A chef at an exclusive Italian restaurant is murdered. Jane investigates the competitive culinary world and old family secrets.
The FBI investigates a string of organ thefts. Jane suspects a doctor with a god complex is involved.
Jane receives a lead that could finally give him peace regarding Red John. He and Lisbon reflect on their future as he prepares to leave.
Jane and Lisbon try to navigate their new romantic relationship while working with the FBI on a case involving an undercover agent who has gone missing.
Lisbon goes undercover as a prison inmate to befriend a woman who can lead the FBI to her dangerous, art-thief boyfriend.
Jane and Lisbon travel to Beirut to work with Erica Flynn, who agrees to help the FBI apprehend her boyfriend, a courier for terrorist organizations, in exchange for amnesty.
The FBI investigates a murder linked to a counterfeit diamond operation. The case hits close to home for Lisbon when she realizes an old flame might be involved.
A colonel from Abbott's past, who could ruin his career, is murdered. Jane investigates, forcing Abbott to confront a difficult decision.
An FBI agent is murdered, and the investigation leads to a DEA raid that went wrong. Jane suspects a cover-up within the ranks.
Lisbon's younger brother, Jimmy, becomes a key witness in a murder investigation, forcing Lisbon to confront her family's troubled past.

episodios.titulo: T7:E8 - The Whites of His Eyes
episodios.sinopsis: A witness in a murder trial is targeted by assassins. Jane and the FBI team must protect her while trying to uncover who wants her dead.
The FBI investigates a murder at a convention for professional psychics. Jane enjoys debunking the fakes while searching for the killer.
A group of armored car robbers pulls off a daring heist. Jane uses his observation skills to predict their next move.
A con man claiming to have psychic powers is murdered. Jane investigates, drawing parallels to his own past.
A serial killer known as "Lazarus" resurfaces, and Jane suspects he may have psychic abilities, or is being aided by someone who does.
As Jane and Lisbon prepare for their wedding, the serial killer Lazarus makes a final, desperate attempt to elude capture, putting their happiness in jeopardy.

sinopsis: Follows the adventures of a mother and daughter who share a magical gift.

episodios.sinopsis: Cassie Nightingale is newly widowed, but so busy with her store, her daughter Grace, and her stepchildren, Brandon and Lori, that she has little time to reflect. Complications arise when John, an old college friend, comes to town.
As Middleton anticipates an ice storm, Cassie's cousin Abigail returns. Sam and Cassie try to help Grace and Nick overcome their fears.
Cassie tries to get a hesitant Sam to accept Grace's Mothers' Day gift. Ryan's sister arrives for a visit. Eve and Linda struggle to see eye-to-eye on the best way to run the Bistro.
Cassie gives a magical birdhouse to a new neighbor. Grace, Brandon and Lori try to plan a surprise party for Cassie. Sam is upset when Linda threatens to take Nick back to New York.

When a visiting chef is unable to make any food for the town's heritage festival, Cassie, with Grace's help, uses her magic to make sure everyone gets fed. Sam and Linda deal with Nick's uncharacteristic behavior.
Cassie plays matchmaker for two of her shop's customers. Grace is accused of shoplifting. Brandon and Lori try to help Nick when they find out he's being blackmailed.
Lori is attracted to a former classmate who's now in the military. Grace is hurt when she learns that Nick is the one who's been shoplifting, but covers for him when he's caught.
Cassie is questioned when money goes missing from the Heritage festival fund. Grace tries to get Nick to confess to the shoplifting. Ryan decides to accept the job offer in Chicago.
Cassie and Sam seem ready to take their relationship to the next level, but Sam's ex-wife, Linda, is determined to win him back. Grace prepares for her driving test.
Cassie decides to temporarily homeschool Grace. Linda tries to get more involved in Nick's life, much to his dismay. Stephanie is struggling to keep the Bistro afloat.
Cassie is surprised to learn that her Обычно calm Abigail is in therapy. Sam is determined to get to the bottom of a medical mystery. Grace runs for class president.

Cassie helps a young couple accept their families' differences. Sam is concerned when Linda makes an important decision about Nick's future without consulting him. Abigail offers Stephanie some dating advice.
Cassie's mischievous cousin Abigail is back in Middleton, and she's got a few surprises in store for the entire town. Grace gets a much-anticipated birthday gift from Cassie.
Cassie encourages Sam to take a risk with a new medical treatment for a patient. Abigail is propositioned by a surprising admirer. Grace tries to get Nick and Noah to make amends.
Cassie gives a speech at a regional conference for B&B owners. Sam supports Eve when she makes a brave decision about her future. Martha is determined to find out the secret of a new couple in town.

When a health inspector threatens to shut down the Heritage Festival, Cassie, with some help from her friends, must use a little magic to save the day. Linda makes a surprising decision about her future.
Cassie tries to help John, her former college friend, reconnect with his estranged brother. Grace is chosen to sing the national anthem at the upcoming minor league baseball game.

episodios.titulo: T2:E10 - Not Getting Married Today, Part 1
episodios.sinopsis: Cassie and Sam's wedding is just days away, but their plans are thrown into disarray when Sam gets a once-in-a-lifetime job offer on the other side of the country.
Cassie and Sam are still going strong, but they are keeping their relationship a secret from Grace and Nick. Middleton is abuzz with the news of a new flower shop opening in town.

episodios.titulo: T3:E2 - Without Magic for a Spell
episodios.sinopsis: When Cassie's magic seems to be fading, she must find a way to get it back before it's too late. Sam is faced with a difficult decision when a former patient returns to Middleton.
Cassie decides to run for mayor of Middleton, but she faces some stiff competition. Grace and Nick get caught up in a time loop, reliving the same day over and over again.

episodios.titulo: T3:E4 - How to Say, 'I Love You!'
episodios.sinopsis: Cassie helps a newly engaged couple plan their wedding. Sam struggles to find the right way to tell Cassie how he feels about her. Grace gets a part-time job at the local library.
Cassie and the rest of Middleton prepare to say goodbye to a beloved resident. Sam tries to help Nick cope with a devastating loss. Grace and Noah's friendship takes an unexpected turn.
Cassie, Grace, and Abigail embark on a road trip to Cassie's alma mater. Sam is left in charge of Grey House, and he quickly learns that running a B&B is harder than it looks.

episodios.titulo: T3:E7 - In Sickness and in Health
episodios.sinopsis: When Sam gets sick, Cassie must use her magic to help him get better. Grace volunteers at the local hospital and discovers a hidden talent for helping others.
Cassie helps a mother and daughter reconnect after years of estrangement. Sam considers making a major career change. Grace and Nick prepare for the school formal.
Cassie hosts a family reunion at Grey House, but things don't go exactly as planned. Sam makes a surprising discovery about his past. Abigail considers a new business venture.

episodios.titulo: T3:E10 - Not Getting Married Today, Part 2
episodios.sinopsis: It's the day of Cassie and Sam's wedding, but a series of mishaps threatens to derail their special day. Grace and Nick make a decision about their future.
Cassie and Sam, now newlyweds, are enjoying their honeymoon when they are called back to Middleton to help a new family in town. Grace and Nick adjust to their new blended family.
Cassie helps Martha plan the annual Middleton Fall Festival. Sam is stumped by a mysterious illness affecting several of his patients. Grace enters a corn maze competition.

Cassie's foster father, Arthur, arrives in Middleton for a surprise visit. Sam tries to help a patient who is reluctant to undergo a life-saving surgery. Abigail and Stephanie compete for the same man.
Cassie, Sam, Grace, and Nick go on a family camping trip, but their plans are disrupted by a series of unexpected events. Martha takes charge of the Middleton Historical Society.
A mysterious guest at Grey House piques Cassie's curiosity. Sam helps a patient who is struggling with memory loss. Grace discovers a hidden talent for writing.
Cassie plays matchmaker for two unlikely people. Sam is forced to confront his past when a former colleague comes to Middleton. Nick tries to help a friend in need.

episodios.titulo: T4:E7 - Til Death Do Us Part
episodios.sinopsis: Cassie helps a young woman who believes her house is haunted. Sam investigates a string of mysterious accidents in Middleton. Grace and Noah's relationship is put to the test.
Cassie organizes a charity fashion show, but things go awry when the main designer pulls out at the last minute. Sam helps a patient who is afraid of needles. Abigail considers a new career path.

episodios.titulo: T4:E9 - How to Make a Middleton Quilt
episodios.sinopsis: Cassie and the women of Middleton work together to create a special quilt for a local charity auction. Sam is faced with a difficult ethical dilemma. Grace makes a decision about her future.
It's the day of Tara and Brandon's wedding, but a series of unexpected events threatens to ruin their special day. Cassie and Sam make a big decision about their future.
Cassie and Sam, along with Grace and Nick, travel to the town of Collinsville to search for a mythical healing tree. Martha plans a surprise for her husband's anniversary.

The search for the Forever Tree continues, leading Cassie and Sam to make a surprising discovery. Grace and Nick meet some interesting new people in Collinsville. Abigail and Stephanie deal with a B&B crisis.
Cassie and Sam finally get to enjoy their honeymoon, but their romantic getaway is interrupted by a series of strange occurrences. Grace starts her internship at the Mayor's office.

A prince visits Middleton, and Martha is determined to make his stay unforgettable. Cassie helps a guest at Grey House who is searching for a long-lost love. Grace struggles with her college applications.
Cassie hosts a tea party at Grey House, but a valuable teapot goes missing. Sam deals with a demanding patient. Abigail's new business venture hits a snag.

Grace accompanies Nick on a road trip to visit his dream college, but the trip takes an unexpected turn. Cassie helps a couple find their way back to each other. Martha launches a new town initiative.
Cassie, Sam, Nick, and Grace go on a family vacation to the lake house, but their relaxing getaway is anything but. Abigail and Donovan's relationship heats up.
A treasure hunt in Middleton brings the whole town together. Cassie helps a guest at Grey House uncover a family secret. Grace makes a difficult decision about her future.
Middleton prepares for the arrival of a rare comet, and Cassie uses the special occasion to help her friends and family make important wishes. Sam receives some unexpected news.
It's graduation day for Grace and Nick, and Cassie and Sam couldn't be prouder. As one chapter closes, another begins, with new adventures on the horizon for the residents of Middleton.
Cassie and Sam celebrate their first wedding anniversary. A mysterious new guest at Grey House has Abigail and Cassie intrigued. Stephanie meets a charming stranger.

Middleton's annual Chili Cook-Off is underway, and the competition is fierce. Cassie helps Joy, the new Grey House guest, uncover a connection to the Merriwick family. Adam and Stephanie's relationship blossoms.

Cassie, Abigail, and Joy work together to uncover the mystery behind a broken clock that belonged to their ancestor. Sam helps Martha find a solution to a town problem. Stephanie gets a surprising offer.
Cassie hosts a dinner party to welcome Joy to Middleton. Sam gets a visit from an old friend who needs his help. Abigail and Donovan face a new obstacle in their relationship.
Cassie, Abigail, and Joy create a mandala to help them focus their energy and uncover more family secrets. Sam helps Martha organize a wellness retreat. Stephanie makes a bold career move.

A series of recurring dreams leads Cassie, Abigail, and Joy to a surprising discovery about their Merriwick heritage. Sam counsels a patient struggling with a difficult decision. Adam plans a romantic surprise for Stephanie.

Middleton prepares for its annual Halloween festival, and Cassie, Abigail, and Joy are tasked with creating a magical tableau. Sam helps a patient overcome their fear of Halloween. Donovan tries to break the curse on his family.
A batch of magical chocolates from Cassie's shop has unexpected effects on the residents of Middleton. Sam deals with a hospital crisis. Abigail and Donovan make a decision about their future.

Joy renovates a historic Middleton loft, uncovering a hidden message from the past. Cassie helps Sam prepare for a prestigious medical conference. Stephanie and Adam face a challenge in their relationship.
A rare bird sighting in Middleton brings unexpected visitors to town. Cassie, Abigail, and Joy solve the final mystery of the Merriwick treasure. Sam makes a life-changing decision.
The Merriwick cousins prepare for Joy's wedding, but a mysterious series of events threatens to derail their plans. Sam receives an unexpected job offer. Adam returns to Middleton with a surprise.
Cassie, Abigail, and Joy investigate the origins of the mysterious velvet pouches they received. Sam considers his job offer. Stephanie and Adam adjust to their new reality.
A special delivery to Grey House leads the Merriwick cousins on a new quest. Sam makes a decision about his career. Martha plans a Middleton bicentennial celebration.
Cassie, Abigail, and Joy participate in a town-wide exchange program, leading to unexpected discoveries. Sam adjusts to his new role at the hospital. Donovan's mother visits Middleton.
Middleton's annual kite festival brings romance and adventure. The Merriwick cousins get closer to solving the mystery of the pouches. Stephanie receives some surprising news.

A wishing well in Middleton grants some unexpected wishes. Cassie helps Joy prepare for her wedding. Sam counsels a patient who is struggling to cope with a loss. Abigail and Donovan face a new challenge.
The Merriwick cousins combine their magic to protect their family legacy. Sam performs a risky surgery. Martha's bicentennial plans hit a snag. Stephanie makes a decision about her future.
Middleton hosts its first-ever 'Middleton Marathon,' and the competition is fierce. Cassie, Abigail, and Joy uncover a crucial clue in their quest. Sam helps a former rival.
The search for the missing component of the Merriwick amulet intensifies. Cassie has a vision that could change everything. Sam and Adam team up for a medical mission.
It's the day of Joy and Zoey's wedding, and the Merriwick cousins finally piece together the clues to break the curse. As one chapter ends, new beginnings await the beloved residents of Middleton.

sinopsis: A high school chemistry teacher diagnosed with inoperable lung cancer turns to manufacturing and selling methamphetamine in order to secure his family's future.

episodios.sinopsis: Diagnosed with terminal lung cancer, chemistry teacher Walter White teams up with former student Jesse Pinkman to cook and sell crystal meth.
Walt and Jesse try to dispose of the bodies of two drug dealers, but complications arise with one of them, Krazy-8, who is still alive.

episodios.titulo: T1:E3 - ...And the Bag's in the River
episodios.sinopsis: Walt is tormented by the decision of whether to kill Krazy-8, while Skyler grows suspicious of Walt's behavior. Jesse struggles with his conscience.
Walt finally reveals his cancer diagnosis to his family. Jesse attempts to cook meth on his own, with disastrous results.
Walt rejects financial help from his wealthy former colleagues. Jesse tries to get a legitimate job but is drawn back to Walt.
Walt, undergoing chemotherapy, shaves his head and adopts the alias 'Heisenberg' to deal with a dangerous distributor named Tuco Salamanca.
Walt and Jesse struggle to produce a large quantity of meth for Tuco, leading them to steal necessary chemicals.
After witnessing Tuco's violent nature, Walt and Jesse fear for their lives and contemplate their next move.
Walt and Jesse are kidnapped by an unhinged Tuco and taken to a remote desert hideout with his disabled uncle.

episodios.titulo: T2:E3 - Bit by a Dead Bee
episodios.sinopsis: To explain his disappearance, Walt fakes a fugue state. Jesse is interrogated by Hank and the DEA.
Jesse is kicked out of his parents' house and spirals downward. Skyler grows more distant from Walt due to his secrecy.
Walt and Jesse begin to establish their own distribution network. Hank struggles with the aftermath of the Tuco shootout.
Jesse confronts a pair of meth addicts who robbed Skinny Pete, leading him to a squalid house with a neglected child.
Walt expands his territory, gaining notoriety as 'Heisenberg.' Hank is transferred to El Paso and encounters the dangers of the cartel.
When Badger is arrested, Walt and Jesse hire a flamboyant, morally flexible lawyer named Saul Goodman.
Believing his cancer has worsened, Walt pressures Jesse into a marathon meth cook in the desert, where they become stranded.
Walt learns his cancer is in remission, leading to an identity crisis. Skyler throws him a party, where he acts erratically.
After Combo is murdered, Jesse spirals into drug use. Saul introduces Walt to a cautious, high-level distributor named Gus Fring.
Walt misses the birth of his daughter to complete a deal with Gus. He later watches Jesse's girlfriend, Jane, die from a heroin overdose.
Skyler uncovers Walt's lies and demands a separation. Jane's grieving father, an air traffic controller, makes a fatal error, causing a mid-air collision over Albuquerque.
Walt grapples with Skyler's decision to leave him. Jesse confronts his demons in rehab. Gus offers Walt $3 million for three months of his time.
Walt tries to reconcile with Skyler. Saul helps Jesse buy his aunt's house. Two mysterious cousins cross the border, seeking Walt.
Skyler reveals her affair with Ted to Walt. Walt forces his way back into the family home, escalating tensions.
Walt struggles with Skyler's coldness. Jesse starts cooking and selling his own, inferior blue meth. Hank aggressively pursues the 'Heisenberg' case.
Gus attempts to lure Walt back into business by showing him a state-of-the-art superlab. Hank's investigation gets closer to Jesse.
Walt accepts Gus's offer. He narrowly saves Jesse from Hank, who is closing in on the RV meth lab.
Hank brutally assaults Jesse, leading to his suspension. Jesse threatens to expose Walt. The Salamanca cousins attack Hank.
Jesse is hospitalized. Walt visits Hank, who is in critical condition after the attack. Gus takes an interest in Jesse.
Jesse resumes cooking in the superlab with Walt. Hank's medical bills become a source of stress for Skyler and Marie.
Obsessed with contamination, Walt refuses to cook until he and Jesse can eliminate a single fly from the superlab.
Skyler becomes more involved in Walt's money laundering. Jesse gets involved with Andrea, a fellow NA member, and her young son, Brock.
Jesse seeks revenge on drug dealers who used Andrea's younger brother. Walt intervenes to protect Jesse from Gus's wrath.
Gus plans to kill Walt and replace him with Gale. To save himself, Walt orders Jesse to kill Gale.
In the aftermath of Gale's murder, Gus makes a chilling statement to Walt and Jesse about their expendability.
Walt buys an untraceable gun to protect himself from Gus. Jesse struggles with guilt and becomes increasingly reckless.
Jesse throws chaotic, drug-fueled parties at his house. Marie struggles with Hank's bitter recovery and reverts to shoplifting. Skyler pressures Walt to buy the car wash.
Walt and Skyler rehearse a story about Walt's gambling addiction to explain their sudden wealth to Hank and Marie. Mike warns Walt about Jesse.
Jesse accompanies Mike on collections, boosting his confidence. Walt fears Jesse's loyalty is shifting to Gus.
Skyler becomes increasingly fearful of Walt's dangerous life. Walt's ego inflates as he asserts, 'I am the one who knocks.'
Jesse confesses his guilt over killing Gale to his NA support group. Walt gives Jesse a ricin cigarette to poison Gus.
Gus's backstory is revealed, including his past with Don Eladio and Hector Salamanca, explaining his motives and meticulous nature.
Walt and Jesse have a brutal fight after Walt plants a tracking device on Jesse's car. Gus takes Jesse to Mexico to teach the cartel how to cook blue meth.
Jesse, Gus, and Mike travel to Mexico to meet Don Eladio. Gus enacts his revenge on the cartel by poisoning them.
Gus threatens Walt's entire family, telling him he is fired. Walt discovers Skyler gave most of his money to Ted, leaving him trapped and desperate.
Brock is poisoned, and Jesse believes Walt is responsible. Walt manipulates Jesse into helping him against Gus.
Walt teams up with Hector Salamanca to execute a plan to kill Gus Fring in a dramatic showdown at the nursing home.
With Gus dead, Walt, Jesse, and Mike work to destroy evidence, including security footage stored on Gus's laptop.
Mike is interrogated by the DEA. Lydia Rodarte-Quayle, a Madrigal executive connected to Gus, is introduced. Walt forms a new partnership with Jesse and Mike.
Walt, Jesse, and Mike start a new meth operation using a pest control company as a front.
It's Walt's 51st birthday. Skyler, terrified of Walt, stages a breakdown in the pool to get the children away from him.
The crew pulls off a daring train heist to steal a massive quantity of methylamine, but it ends with a tragic, unforeseen consequence.
Mike and Jesse want to get out of the meth business and sell their share of the methylamine. Walt refuses, determined to build his empire.
Walt expands his operation, negotiating a deal with Declan's crew. He ultimately kills Mike when Mike refuses to give up the names of Gus's former employees.
Walt eliminates Mike's nine associates in prison. His meth empire runs smoothly for months. Hank makes a shocking discovery connecting Walt to Gale.
Hank confronts Walt about being Heisenberg. Jesse, wracked with guilt over his blood money, tries to give it away.
Skyler reveals the truth about Walt to Marie. Jesse is taken into custody and interrogated by Hank.
Walt records a false confession video implicating Hank as Heisenberg. Jesse learns the truth about Walt poisoning Brock.
Jesse, enraged by the truth about Brock, teams up with Hank to take Walt down. Walt hires Jack's crew to kill Jesse.
Hank and Gomez, with Jesse's help, lure Walt into a trap in the To'hajiilee desert by faking the discovery of his money.
A brutal desert shootout erupts between Jack's crew and Hank and Gomez. Hank is killed, Jesse is captured, and Walt's world crumbles.
Walt is relocated to a remote cabin in New Hampshire. Jesse is enslaved by Jack's crew and forced to cook meth.
Walt returns to Albuquerque to settle his affairs, ensure his family's financial future, exact revenge on Jack's crew, and free Jesse.

sinopsis: Set in the inner sanctum of a family bound together by unfathomable wealth and unchecked power as they build an evangelical megachurch.

episodios.sinopsis: The Quinn family, founders of megachurch U Star, are a powerful and wealthy dynasty. When their charismatic leader, Cal Quinn, announces an ambitious US expansion, the family is poised to catapult into a new stratosphere of wealth and influence.

As Cal and Abi prepare for their US tour, a shock announcement from the US President places their ambitious expansion plans in peril. With the Quinn family reeling, a looming tax audit adds further cause for panic.

As Cal and Abi launch their US campaign, Dion's shocking revelation threatens to derail the U Star expansion. Meanwhile, Issachar's growing suspicions about a rival church place the family in further jeopardy.

While Cal and Abi preach their controversial message in the US, the family's hidden secrets start to unravel at home. When Issachar's investigation hits a dead end, Moses makes a desperate bargain with a dangerous enemy.

With the US expansion gaining momentum, Cal and Abi return to Sydney for a worship festival. But when a televised interview takes an unexpected turn, the family is forced to confront a looming catastrophe.

As the Quinn family faces a public backlash, Cal makes a series of increasingly reckless decisions. With U Star's reputation in tatters, Moses takes matters into his own hands, with devastating consequences.

episodios.titulo: T1:E7 - Be a Fisher of Men
episodios.sinopsis: With Cal in hospital and the US expansion in jeopardy, the Quinn family is forced to choose a new leader. As a bitter power struggle ensues, a startling revelation tears the family apart.
As the family implodes, a shocking betrayal forces the Quinn siblings to choose sides. With the US expansion hanging in the balance, a new leader prepares to take U Star into an uncertain future.

sinopsis: After an unexpected pregnancy, two best friends who are chronically unable to make good decisions decide to co-parent a child.

episodios.sinopsis: When Rosa discovers she is pregnant following a one night stand, best friend Val offers a solution: they will raise the baby together.
With the 20 week scan on the horizon, Rosa and Val are faced with the daunting decision of whether to find out the baby's gender. Val makes a bold career move.
Rosa and Val decide to find a godfather for the baby but struggle to find the ideal candidate. Val finds herself navigating an unexpected HR complaint.
Rosa and Val attend Val's godson's christening, where Rosa meets a charming stranger. Val contends with a series of workplace micro-aggressions.
Rosa and Val go on a hen do, but the weekend takes an unexpected turn. Val makes a decision that could jeopardise her career.
Val throws Rosa a surprise baby shower, but tensions rise when Rosa's estranged mother arrives uninvited. Val faces the consequences of her actions.
As Rosa's due date approaches, she and Val try to create the perfect birthing plan. Val is offered an exciting new opportunity, forcing her to make a difficult choice.
Rosa goes into labour, and she and Val navigate the chaos of childbirth. As they welcome the new arrival, they look towards an uncertain future.

sinopsis: Diego de la Vega returns to California to avenge his father's murder. After being elected Zorro, he begins a struggle against the Governor, the evil leader of the Chinese community and a secret society, all while trying to win Lolita's heart.

episodios.sinopsis: California, 1834. The town of Los Angeles is a place of injustice and inequality. While the people look for a savior, Diego de la Vega is chosen by his predecessor to become the new Zorro.
Diego wears the Zorro costume for the first time to avenge a murder, but Lolita, his past love, suspects him of being the murderer. Meanwhile, the governor discovers that Zorro is still alive.
A robbery at the hacienda and the subsequent arrest of one of his workers leads Diego to take justice into his own hands and discover that not everything is as it seems in his family's business.
Some natives are accused of attacking the convoy that was carrying the taxes from Los Angeles. Zorro suspects that someone else is responsible for the robbery and tries to find out the truth.
The Russians threaten the stability of California by trying to seize one of the canyons in the region. Zorro has to avoid the sale to protect the interests of California.
Lolita organizes a masked ball to raise funds to compensate the peasants who lost their lands due to the Russians. This party will be the scene of Zorro's reappearance.
One of Zorro's followers is captured by the governor, who tries to make him confess Zorro's identity. The hero must rescue him to preserve his secret.
While Lolita begins to trust Zorro and distrust the governor, he and the Bear Clan make a pact to fight the common enemy: Zorro, whom they seek to unmask.
Zorro is captured. While in prison, he must confront his past to escape and face his captors once and for all.

episodios.titulo: T1:E10 - El baile de las urracas (The Dance of the Magpies)
episodios.sinopsis: The final battle for California begins. Zorro will face all his enemies in a fight to the death. His identity is revealed, and the future of California rests in his hands.

sinopsis: Based on the best-selling novel by John Grisham, 'The Firm' is a new drama series that continues the story of attorney Mitchell McDeere and his family, 10 years after the events of the novel and film.

episodios.sinopsis: Ten years after the events of the film, Mitch McDeere and his family emerge from the Federal Witness Protection Program to confront new dangers and old enemies.
Mitch takes on a pro bono murder case that hits close to home, while Abby tries to adjust to their new life and Ray deals with the firm's demanding clients.
Mitch defends a client accused of murdering a judge, a case that puts him at odds with a powerful political figure.
While investigating a wrongful death suit, Mitch uncovers a conspiracy involving a pharmaceutical company.
Mitch represents a woman whose son was killed in a hazing incident at a prestigious military academy.
The firm takes on a case involving a whistleblower who exposed illegal practices at a major corporation.
Mitch is hired to defend a man accused of terrorism, a case that draws unwanted attention from the government.
A seemingly straightforward divorce case takes a dangerous turn when Mitch discovers a link to organized crime.
Mitch and Abby's past comes back to haunt them when an old enemy resurfaces.
The firm investigates a series of mysterious deaths at a nursing home, uncovering a sinister plot.
Mitch must defend Ray when he is accused of a crime he didn't commit.
A high-profile murder case forces Mitch to confront his own moral boundaries.
The conspiracy surrounding Sarah Holt deepens, putting Mitch and his family in greater danger.
Mitch races against time to find evidence that will clear his client and expose a cover-up.
The firm deals with the fallout from a data breach that compromises sensitive client information.
Mitch uncovers a vital clue that could blow the lid off the conspiracy, but it puts him directly in the crosshairs.
As the stakes get higher, Mitch must make difficult choices to protect those he loves.
The lines between friend and foe blur as Mitch gets closer to the truth.
A shocking betrayal forces Mitch to question everything he thought he knew.
With the conspiracy unraveling, Mitch prepares for a final confrontation with his enemies.
The noose tightens around Mitch as he makes a desperate attempt to expose the truth and save his family.
In a climactic finale, Mitch faces his adversaries, and the fate of his family hangs in the balance.

sinopsis: The story of Ida Ramundo, a widowed schoolteacher, who decides to hide her Jewish heritage to escape the race laws and the war.

episodios.sinopsis: Rome, 1940. Schoolteacher Ida, secretly Jewish, is raped by a German soldier. Her life, already shadowed by war and racial laws, takes a dramatic turn.
Ida gives birth to Useppe. Her older son Nino, initially resentful, grows attached to the baby. Bombings force Ida and Useppe to flee their home.
Ida and Useppe find shelter in a displaced persons' camp. Nino joins the partisans. Useppe shows early signs of a mysterious illness.
The war ends, but hardships continue. Nino, changed by his partisan experience, engages in black market activities. Useppe's health worsens.
Post-war Rome. Ida and Useppe struggle to rebuild their lives. They meet Davide, a Holocaust survivor haunted by his past. Useppe's epileptic seizures become more frequent.
Nino's dangerous lifestyle puts him and the family at risk. Ida desperately tries to protect her sons. Useppe finds a kindred spirit in Davide.
A devastating tragedy shatters the family. Ida is consumed by grief. Useppe's illness progresses, marked by fleeting moments of joy and profound suffering.
Ida confronts overwhelming loss and despair. The narrative concludes, highlighting the enduring and devastating impact of history and war on individual lives.

sinopsis: A continuation of the story of Belgravia. Set in 1871, three decades after the events depicted in the 2020 limited series, the story centers on Frederick Trenchard, the third Lord Trenchard, and his new love interest, Clara Dunn, a young woman who is a newcomer to London society. Unaware that his birth was the product of an affair between his mother Susan and the scoundrel John Bellasis, a troubled childhood has left Frederick deeply insecure, which challenges his courtship of and marriage to Clara.

episodios.sinopsis: Belgravia, 1871. Frederick Trenchard, a successful young businessman, is consumed by his past. His father, Oliver, feels like a failure. At a lavish party, Frederick meets Clara Dunn, a beautiful, intelligent young woman.
Frederick and Clara’s courtship is quickly accepted by many. But Frederick’s insecurities, and the presence of his embittered brother James, threaten to tear them apart.
Frederick and Clara marry. Frederick’s anxieties about his place in the world are thrown into sharp focus when he is accused of stealing another man’s invention.
Frederick grows colder towards Clara, whose friendship with Dr. Ellerby causes further tension. James plots to ruin his brother.
Clara and Frederick fight. Frederick’s insecurities grow, pushing him further away from Clara. She seeks comfort in Dr. Ellerby’s company.
James’s scheme against Frederick seems to be working. Davison, Clara’s maid, tries to warn Clara that her affair with Ellerby will ruin her.
The Trenchards travel to their country home, Glanville, for the summer. Clara hopes the trip will bring her and Frederick closer. James sees an opportunity to strike.
Clara must decide if she can forgive Frederick. James, with his scheme in tatters, makes a desperate move to save himself. The truth of Frederick’s past is finally revealed.

sinopsis: The life of Anderson Silva, also known as 'Spider', the greatest champion in MMA history.

episodios.titulo: T1:E1 - A Aranha Nasce em Curitiba
episodios.sinopsis: In Curitiba, Anderson, raised by his aunt, divides his time between his job at a Burger King and Taekwondo training with his master. He meets Dayane.

episodios.titulo: T1:E2 - O Amor é uma Distração Cara
episodios.sinopsis: Anderson is torn between his fighting career and his relationship with Dayane. His master sees his potential, but Anderson faces obstacles.
Anderson travels to Japan for his first international fight, facing cultural shock and a tough opponent. This experience shapes his future.
Anderson returns to Brazil, still seeking recognition. He struggles to find fights and support, but his determination doesn't waver.

episodios.titulo: T1:E5 - A Luta é a Sua Alma
episodios.sinopsis: Anderson finally gets his shot at the UFC, leading to his legendary reign as middleweight champion and solidifying his status as 'Spider.'

sinopsis: The story of Cristóbal Balenciaga, the enigmatic and extraordinarily talented Spanish designer who defied the conventions of his time and revolutionized the world of fashion.

episodios.sinopsis: Cristóbal Balenciaga presents his first haute couture collection in Paris in 1937. He has left behind a successful career in Spain, but the sophisticated world of Paris fashion proves hostile.
Balenciaga's atelier thrives during the Nazi occupation of Paris, but personal losses and the war's brutality take their toll on him and his team.
The arrival of Christian Dior and his "New Look" challenges Balenciaga's dominance. Balenciaga must redefine his style to stay relevant in the post-war fashion landscape.
Balenciaga faces the issue of unauthorized replicas of his designs and clashes with the powerful American press, while also dealing with personal betrayals.
Balenciaga is commissioned to design Queen Fabiola of Belgium's wedding dress, a project that brings him immense prestige but also intense pressure and scrutiny.
As the world of fashion changes dramatically in the 1960s with the rise of prêt-à-porter, Balenciaga contemplates his legacy and the future of his haute couture house.
